  "text": "In documents, topically coherent segments usually encapsulate a set of consecutive passages that are semantically related [CITATION_1] . However, the topic boundaries between segments are often unavailable a priori. Thus we treat all passage boundaries (e.g., sentence boundaries, paragraph boundaries or pauses between utterances) as possible topic boundaries. To recover the topic boundaries we develop a structured topic segmentation model by integrating ideas from the segmented topic model (Du et al., 2010, STM) and Bayesian segmentation models.",
